<TITLE> 2000 phones out of order </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narayanganj, Apr 17 (bdnews24.com)  Nearly 2000 telephone lines of the state-owned BTCL have been disconnected since Saturday morning. Even telephone connection of the district police superintendent's office, model police station, hospitals, fire station, press club, power agencies & Titas gas are out of order. Abdullah Patwary, the Narayanganj sub divisional engineer of Bangladesh Telecommunications Company Limited told reporters that due to technical problems in the exchange 2000 phones had gone out of order. Most of the government institutions have been affected. He said that experts were on their way from Dhaka to fix the problem. When asked, he could not confirm when the phones may be expected to be working again. bdne
